    "( 10), because q ϕ (z|x n, s n) is proportional to the product of individual Gaussians (or 'experts'), itself is a Gaussian whose mean μ n and variance ν n can be calculated using those of the individual Gaussians:μ μ μ n 𝒩 ( μ μ μ s n ν ν ν s n + ∑ m∈ℳ n μ μ μ m n ν ν ν m n) ⊙ ν ν ν n ν ν ν n 𝒩 (1 + 1 ν ν ν s n + ∑ m∈ℳ n 1 ν ν ν m n) -1 (15)where ⊙ is the Hadamard product.In doing this, q ϕ (z|x n, s n) is modularized into (M + 1) neural networks to handle (2 M - 1) different modality combinations, increasing the model's scalability.",
    "Similar to the modality decoders, we also share parameters of the last few layers of different modality encoders 𝒩f m } m∈ℳ (the gray parts of the encoders in Fig. 1b, middle) to improve generalization.",
    "Handling missing features via padding and maskingFor each modality, as different cells can have different feature sets (for example, genes for RNA modality), it is hard to use a fixed-size neural network to handle these cells.",
    "To remedy this, we first convert x x x m n of variable size into a fixed-size vector for inference.",
    "For modality m, let ℱ m n be the features of cell n and let ℱ m 𝒩 ⋃ n∈𝒩𝒩 ℱ m n be the feature union of all cells."
